==English==

===Etymology===
Derived in humorous reference to [[frontal]].

This word has begun to gain popular acceptance since appearing in the US [[sitcoms]], 'Friends' and 'Scrubs'.

===Adjective===
'''backal'''
# (''humorous'')(''neologism'') Of, relating to, directed toward, or situated at the [[back]].
:* ''full backal nudity''